<h2>Guided search</h2>
<p>This is the guided search, it allows you to specify one filter at a time with as much information as possible. Hopefully you will find what you need at the end of these few steps.</p>

<h2>Step 1: Type</h2>
<p>Choose the types of articles you are interested in.</p>

<%= form_tag(article.guide_path(:category), :method => :get) do -%>
  <div>
    <% @types.each do |type| %>
      <div>
        <%= check_box_tag 'types[]', type.title, checked = is_checked?(session[:types], type.title), id: remove_chars(type.title) %>
        <%= label_tag remove_chars(type.title), type.title %>
      </div>
      <p><%= type.description %></p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <div><%= submit_tag 'Next', :class=>"mock-btn" %></div>
<% end -%>